Key Match Events: Sybrand Engelbrecht received a bizarre reprieve as his dismissal was overturned
Matt Henry finished things, first tempting Sybrand Engelbrecht to pick out Devon Conway, running in from deep square, and then producing a gem which ripped Aryan Dutt's leg stump
Pre-Game Insights: Netherlands are going to need a record here, chasing 323 to win. Their highest successful run chase in ODIs is 291 against Zimbabwe in 2019.
Post-Match Reflections: Mitchell Santner was Player of the Match
Miscellaneous Highlights: New Zealand hung a strong total on half-centuries to Will Young, Tom Latham and Rachin Ravindra, with Daryl Mitchell contributing 48.
Others: This is from stats legend Sampath Bandarupalli: New Zealand is only the second team to take three or more overs to get off the mark in a ODI World Cup game since 1999 (the first edition where we have BBB for all matches). West Indies, in the opening game of the 2003 edition vs South Africa, got their first runs via wide after 3.1 overs.
